{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Several extensions of VDN have been developed, further addressing the factorization of the global Q-value: QMIX (Rashid et al. 2020), QTRAN (Son et al. 2019 (Son et al., 2020)) and QPLEX (Wang et al. 2020c).",
    "QMIX builds upon the foundational framework of VDN but introduces a mixing network to incorporate individual Q-values in a non-linear fashion.",
    "The authors constructed the assumption that the global reward should adhere to a monotonic constraint between the global Q-value and individual Q-values.",
    "This empowers decentralized policies to make effective decisions based on both local observations and information received from neighboring agents.",
    "In contrast, QTRAN addresses this assumption of a monotonic constraint."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Several extensions of VDN have been developed, further addressing the factorization of the global Q-value: QMIX (Rashid et al. 2020), QTRAN (Son et al. 2019 (Son et al., 2020)) and QPLEX (Wang et al. 2020c)."
  ]
}